Source: ufoai
Section: contrib/games
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Yann Dirson <dirson@debian.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4.0.0), dh-buildinfo, libx11-dev, libxext-dev, libjpeg-dev, libvorbis-dev, libglu1-mesa-dev, xlibmesa-gl-dev, libsdl-dev, libsdl-ttf2.0-dev, libarts1-dev, ncurses-dev
Standards-Version: 3.6.1

Package: ufoai
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, ufoai-data (>= 2.2~~svn), ufoai-vid-glx | ufoai-vid, ufoai-snd-sdl | ufoai-snd
Suggests: ufoai-data-music, ufoai-vid, ufoai-snd
Description: UFO: Alien Invasion - build your team and stop the aliens
 "UFO: Alien Invasion" is a game inspired by the XCOM "UFO" series.
 .
 As manager of an international military force dedicated to stop the
 Alien Invasion, you prepare your soldiers and attack the aliens on
 various sites on the Earth.
 .
 The tactical part of the game uses OpenGL, and is based on the Quake2
 engine.  A multiplayer mode is also available.

Package: ufoai-vid-glx
Architecture: any
Provides: ufoai-vid
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: UFO: Alien Invasion - GLX video module
 "UFO: Alien Invasion" is a game inspired by the XCOM "UFO" series.
 .
 UFO:AI comes with several video rendering engines. This is the
 default one, which uses GLX.  Note that not installing the default
 engine will require users to select an alternative manually.

Package: ufoai-vid-sdl
Architecture: any
Provides: ufoai-vid
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: UFO: Alien Invasion - SDL video module
 "UFO: Alien Invasion" is a game inspired by the XCOM "UFO" series.
 .
 UFO:AI comes with several video rendering engines.  This is the
 an alternative one, which uses SDL.  Note that using an alternative
 engine requires manual configuration.

Package: ufoai-snd-sdl
Architecture: any
Provides: ufoai-snd
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: UFO: Alien Invasion - SDL sound support
 "UFO: Alien Invasion" is a game inspired by the XCOM "UFO" series.
 .
 UFO:AI comes with support for several sound systems. This is the
 default sound-support package, which uses SDL.  Note that not
 installing the default engine will require users to select an
 alternative manually using "+set snd_ref <alternative>".

